        "subject": "LU-20023 lnet: set locked primary peer NI DOWN if notified",
        "message": "LU-20023 lnet: set locked primary peer NI DOWN if notified\n\nIf discovery removes a locked primary peer NI,\nthe NI remains present, appears healthy, and so\nmay still be selected for TX.\n\nTreat this as a lpni DOWN event instead.\nThis preserves the NI for identity while preventing\nits use for transmission.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=sanity-lnet\nSigned-off-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I49b1640cc192ec7f4a44b63f09d431d0aef30c50\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64708\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Xinxia Qu <xqu@ddn.com>\nReviewed-by: Cyril Bordage <cbordage@whamcloud.com>\n"
